* change the version number in dips/__init__.py
* edit CHANGES.txt and add a one-line description
* edit README.md if necessary
* commit (and merge, if necessary) to master
* on github, click on the Releases tab and Generate a new release
* build the dist by running python setup.py sdist bdist_wheel
  (if you run python setup.py install, it'll generate .egg as well)
* upload to pypi by running `twine upload dist/*`
* celebrate :)